entry.title: Revert "[//cc] Add MappableSI path to OneCopyRasterBufferProvider"
entry.content:
This reverts commit 031f7c9ee19d8524abd7a1351b2e10de44ac78bf.



Reason for revert: Might cause a test consistency failure on https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/luci.chromium.ci/chromeos-amd64-generic-rel



Apologize for reverting. Please feel free to reland if it is not related, thanks.



Original change's description:

> [//cc] Add MappableSI path to OneCopyRasterBufferProvider

>

> This CL adds a new path to OneCopyRasterBufferProvider that uses

> MappableSharedImage rather than GpuMemoryBuffer. The new path is

> protected by a killswitch. The gist of the change is that rather than

> creating a GpuMemoryBuffer, mapping that in, and then later creating a

> SharedImage from it, the new path directly creates a

> MappableSharedImage (via the new CreateSI() entrypoint), maps that in,

> *and* additionally uses it in the same ways that the SI created from

> the GMB is being used.

>

> One subtlety is that the GMB is created with the size of the

> StagingBuffer, while the SharedImage for the StagingBuffer in its

> current creation point in CopyOnWorkerThread() is created with the

> `resource_size` param passed to PlaybackAndCopyOnWorkerThread(). Thus,

> we would want the MappableSI for the StagingBuffer to be created with

> "both" sizes. Fortunately (and as one would expect), the StagingBuffer

> is initialized with the `resource_size` param, so the two sizes are

> guaranteed to be the same [1].

>

> [1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:cc/raster/one_copy_raster_buffer_provider.cc;l=295-297?q=CopyOnWorker&ss=chromium

entry.title: Change GWS ID assignments for 64-bit Clank experiment to M117+, M118+
entry.content:
We still want to be able to start tracking an experiment from a certain

milestone, but we don't want to end it at that same milestone (in case

we want to collect more data).



Note that M117 is already shipping to Stable, but that's ok, no changes

needed there. We have to, however, merge the change into M118 branch

before it hits Stable, so that it also emits the M117+ ID.



While at it, remove the IDs related to M116. We won't use them. The

experiment shipped mid-M116, and we have no way to filter by

sub-milestone version in Rasta, so the results would be a mixed bag of

pre-shipped and post-shipped data.

entry.title: [web-tests] Always pass test paths to `WPTManifest.get_test_type(...)`
entry.content:
In its original implementation [1], `get_test_type(...)` [1] is called

with URLs, even though the implementation checks a collection of test

file paths. This works for most tests, where the URL matches the path

exactly, but causes `get_test_type(...)` to not recognize variants where

the assumption does not hold.



Since test type is a per-file property, `get_test_type(...)` continues

to accept a file path. Ensure all callers comply, converting a URL to

its path first if necessary.



Also:

* When an item specifies an explicit URL (as variants do), strip the

leading slash `/` to be consistent with implicit URLs without `/`.

* Rename the argument of `extract_reference_list(...)` to `url` to be

consistent with other methods and clarify what is actually passed [2].

* Get the reference list/fuzzy metadata directly from the item for that

URL, instead of iterating the items for that test file. These data are

the same within a file in practice, but it's less correct to rely on

that assumption.



[1]: https://crrev.com/c/3835032

[2]: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:third_party/blink/tools/blinkpy/web_tests/port/base.py;l=970;drc=f9c58cec02ed8a314e17a6837007049b7cd6d4a1;bpv=0;bpt=0

entry.title: Simplify WebAppToolbarButtonContainer color handling.
entry.content:
Now that PWA windows make sure toolbar button colors are set

correctly in their color providers, we no longer need a bunch

of custom logic to update colors of various toolbar buttons.

This includes removal of:

- DownloadToolbarButtonView::SetIconColor

- ToolbarIconContainerView::SetIconColor

- WebAppMenuButton::SetColor (and set_icon)

- WindowControlsOverlayToggleButton::SetColor



WebAppMenuButton and WindowControlsOverlayToggleButton also get

a GetIconSize override, to maintain the previous behavior where

the icon size was derived from the passed in vector icon, rather

than being hardcoded to the toolbar button icon size.



Finally, CustomTabBarView still does use a WebAppMenuButton in a

context where a color override is needed. That is implemented by

subclassing WebAppMenuButton and overriding GetForegroundColor.

entry.title: [headless] Add support for independent PRIMARY and clipboard buffers
entry.content:
Both new and old headless use ui::ClipboardNonBacked to implement

clipboard that is independent from the underlying platform clipboard

thus allowing running clipboard tests in parallel processes.



Existing ui::ClipboardNonBacked implementation only supports single

clipboard buffer which creates inconsistency with headful Chrome

running on Linux and Fuchsia where kSelection clipboard buffer is

supported. Mac also supports kDrag clipboard buffer type.



This CL refactors ui::ClipboardNonBacked implementation so that

it supports buffer types other than clipboard.



ClipboardBuffer::kSelection and kDrag are not supported on all

platforms, however kCopyPaste is available everywhere.



Note that since previous implementation used to ignore buffer type the clients that specify unsupported buffer type will now crash.



Also: clipboard_non_backed_unittest.cc are now exercised on all

systems where headless Chrome is supported. This includes Linux,

Windows and Mac.

entry.title: [Switch Access] Don't show setup guide in tests, reducing flakes
entry.content:
The switch access tests in Lacros can flake when the setup guide

is shown and steals focus. This doesn't happen in Ash which usually

completes the whole test before the setup guide is visible. However,

in Lacros, which is slower to launch, the setup guide was stealing

focus in the middle of the test.



The code to keep the setup guide from showing is copied from

TestControllerAsh::SetAssistiveTechnologyEnabled which does the

same work.
